Text: FW Gas QuestionForwarded by Vivien PhamHOUECT on PM From Tracy nronXgate on AM To Vivien CT cc Subject FW Gas Question Vivien Can you tell me if the gas expense for Harbor Cogen is being booked to company Can you tell me what is happening with this Thanks Tracy Original Message From Evans Casey Sent Tuesday May PM To Greene Tracy Subject RE Gas Question I dont have any of the TAGG specifics but the trader here says it is approximately M Supposedly the individual in Gas Settlements that has been making the manual entries each month is Vivien Phamwe Power just arent seeing it flow through to us to record to our dpr Maybe she has some info that would help us all From Tracy nronXgate on PM To Casey nron cc Subject RE Gas Question Im looking into it I tie out each month with the gas desks on our liquidations So whatever has liquidated out of TAGG is what gets booked I havent noticed the West desk being off in there liquidations Do you which gas deskbook this should be with Do you have amounts or deals numbers Original Message From Evans Casey Sent Tuesday May PM To Tracy NRON Cc Chang Fran Dunton Heather Law Samantha Subject Gas Question Tracy The West Power desk has been involved in a deal since last July whereby we Power Desk run a generator for a third party Harbor Cogen with gas we purchased from the Houston gas desk Here is my questionhave you ever seen an entry booked by the gas desk charging West Power for the gas cost because West Power has never recorded this gas cost The gas book name for West Power is EPMI West Coast if that helps Thanks Casey
